ZCZC EE58
EXTENDED OUTLOOK
MONDAY TO THURSDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 082300 UTC
DURING MONDAY EVENING AND TUESDAY AN AREA OF LOW PRESSURE 991 WILL LIE
W OF IRELAND WITH CYCLONIC CONDITIONS ACROSS MOST SEA AREAS. ANOTHER DISCRETE
LOW PRESSURE CENTRE WILL FORM NEAR SHETLAND THEN MOV NWARDS LATER TUESDAY.
A SECONDARY LOW WILL RUN INTO FITZROY DURING TUESDAY EVENING. HIGH PRESSURE
WILL LIE NEAR ICELAND AND DEVELOP LATER OVER THE N SEA. A SIMILAR PRESSURE
PATTERN WILL PERSIST THROUGH WEDNESDAY WITH COMPLEX LOW DEVELOPING OVER THE
BRITISH ISLES AND SLWY FLN. THIS LOW WILL MOV SWARDS THROUGH THURSDAY WITH
RIDGE CONDITIONS FM THE ICELANDIC HIGH PRESSURE EXTENDING OVER NERN BRITAIN.
WINDS WILL BE STRG IN ATLANTIC SEA AREAS DURING MONDAY EVENING AND TUESDAY
MORNING WITH OCCASIONAL GALES IN FITZROY SOLE AND SHANNON MODERATING TO
OCNL STRG LATER BUT WITH FURTHER GALES IN FITZROY. WINDS WILL CONTINUE OCNL
STRG IN THE ATLANTIC THROUGH WEDNESDAY POSS GALES FOR A TIME IN BISCAY AND
FITZROY. STRG N WINDS WILL DEVELOP IN THE ATLANTIC DURING THURSDAY
